<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Exercise 3 - A Simple Python Script</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Create a new directory (folder) in your 'home' directory</li>
            <ul><li>You can do this either using the command line (mkdir) or by using Konqueror.</li></ul>
        <li>Using your editor of choice, create a new file, and save it as &quot;hello-world.py&quot;</li>
        <li>Type the following code into your file</li>
        <pre>print "Hello World" </pre>
        <li>Save the file</li>
        <li>Run it from the command line by typing</li>
        <pre>python hello-world.py </pre>
    </ol>
    <a target='new' href='py-html/hello1.htm'>Example</a>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Exercise 4 - Making the Script More Useful</h1>
    <br />
    <ul>
        <li>We had to instruct Python to run the script:</li>
        <pre>python hello-world.py</pre>
        <li>It would be better if we could run the script directly:</li>
        <pre>./hello-world.py</pre>
        <li>To do this, we need a way of telling Linux that Python is needed.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Exercise 4 - Making the Script More Useful</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Start a new file, hello2.py, enter the following:</li>
        <pre>#!/usr/bin/env python</pre>
        <pre>print "Hello World"</pre>
        <li>Save the file, and Run it from the command line by typing</li>
        <pre>./hello2.py</pre>
        <li>This didn't work, why ?</li>
    </ol>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Exercise 4 - Making the Script More Useful</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Start a new file, hello2.py, enter the following:</li>
        <pre>#!/usr/bin/env python</pre>
        <pre>print "Hello World"</pre>
        <li>Save the file, and Run it from the command line by typing</li>
        <pre>./hello2.py</pre>
        <li>This didn't work, why ?</li>
        <li>We have to set the file's mode first, to make it executable...</li>
        <pre>chmod u+x hello2.py </pre>
    </ol>
    <a target='new' href='py-html/hello2.htm'>Example</a>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Exercise 5 - Doing it with a Function</h1>
    <p>We'll look at functions in detail later, for now we will
       just have a simple one...
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Start a new file, hello3.py, enter the following:</li>
        <pre>#!/usr/bin/env python</pre>
        <pre>def hello():</pre>
        <pre>    print "Hello World"</pre>
        <pre>hello()</pre>
        <li>Save the file, set its mode and run it from the command line by typing</li>
        <pre>./hello3.py</pre>
    </ol>
    <a target='new' href='py-html/hello3.htm'>Example</a>
</div>

